Vụ kiện giúp hôn nhân đồng tính ở Mỹ hợp pháp (Học qua tin)
Vụ kiện của cặp đôi April DeBoer và Jayne Rows đã góp phần giúp hôn nhân đồng tính được Tòa án Tối cao Mỹ thông qua. Bạn có thể học thêm từ mới về kiện tụng qua video ngắn sau.
April DeBoer finally got what she always wanted -- a chance to wed her partner, Jayne Rowse.
The couple had previously sued the State of Michigan when, according to the state's past same-sex marriage ban, they were denied the right to jointly adopt children.
DeBoer explained her position earlier this year.
(SOUNDBITE) (English) APRIL DEBOER, PLAINTIFF IN SAME-SEX MARRIAGE CASE BEING HEARD BY U.S. SUPREME COURT, SAYING:
"We spend family time together. We teach the kids to do chores. We teach the kids to ride bikes. We teach the kids. You know, there's no difference in our family."
Their lawsuit helped lead to the U.S. Supreme Court's historic legalization of gay marriage, nationwide.
(SOUNDBITE) (English) FEDERAL JUDGE BERNARD FRIEDMAN, SAYING:
"They are such dynamic people, such positive people that they continue to do what they're doing and make a difference in everybody's life."
